Author: Alexfrog#1338
Content:
>yes but it is criminal to corrupt mainet NN operators : investors, community and coin dev will be furious and I'll go to jail with everyone here

This is not the right way to think about it.   A blockchain must be secure against attacks, thats the entire point.  No one should trust something if a bad actor could break it without tremendous difficulty

Author: Alexfrog#1338
Content:
>  I'm thinking about the 400 blocks reverted/reorged on ETC and about XVG cases

This is what KMD DPoW is designed to prevent.  You cannot do a deep chain reorg because some of those blocks got notorized.   Alternately, if no notorizations happened, then you cannot trust that a transaction has been confirmed

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content:
```#!/bin/bash
file="$HOME/2019NNtestnet/iguana/m_notary_testnet"
while IFS= read -r line
do
    ip=$( echo $line | grep addnotary | sed 's/[{}]//g' | sed 's_\\__g' | sed 's_"__g' | sed 's=curl --url http://127.0.0.1:7776 --data agent:iguana,method:addnotary,ipaddr:==')
    if [ ${#ip} -gt 1 ]; then
    echo $ip
    fi
done <"$file"
```
